An Act relative to membership updates for the Massachusetts Food Policy Council.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 6C of chapter 20 of the General Laws, as most recently amended by
2 section 49 of chapter 7 of the acts of 2023, is hereby amended by striking out subsection (a) and
3 inserting in place thereof the following subsection:-
4 (a) There shall be established a Massachusetts food policy council, hereinafter referred to
5 as the council. The council shall consist of 20 members, 1 of whom shall be a member of the
6 house of representatives; 1 of whom shall be a member of the senate; 1 of whom shall be a
7 member of the house of representatives who shall be appointed by the minority leader of the
8 house of representatives; 1 of whom shall be a member of the senate who shall be appointed by
9 the minority leader of the senate; 1 of whom shall be the commissioner of agricultural resources,
10 or the commissioner's designee; 1 of whom shall be the commissioner of public health, or the
11 commissioner's designee; 1 of whom shall be the commissioner of elementary and secondary
12 education, or the commissioner's designee; 1 of whom shall be the commissioner of
